    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework for non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending satisfies all acceptance criteria for 12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors at or above required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted in the regulatory context given that ASTM F1717 represents the standard regulatory test configuration and the decision consequence is Medium. Aggregate credibility is sufficient for the intended regulatory submission supporting a 510(k) clearance decision.",
